{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac dedicated hosts to double your macOS CI capacity."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide"],"anchor":"Related-Guides","title":"Related Guides"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineBundle","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CloneManager","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Compatibility","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RestoreImageManager","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineState"],"anchor":"Key-Types","title":"Key Types"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"AWS EC2 Mac instances provide bare-metal Apple Silicon hardware in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"cloud. Each EC2 Mac host can run a single macOS instance natively, but"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with Spooktacular you can run "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"two","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" macOS virtual machines per host —"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"doubling your CI runner capacity without adding hardware."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This guide covers the complete setup: from allocating a dedicated host"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to running a production GitHub Actions fleet on EC2 Mac."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Prerequisites","anchor":"Prerequisites"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before you begin, ensure you have:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"AWS account"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" with EC2 Mac instance access (may require a service","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"quota increase for ","type":"text"},{"code":"mac2.metal","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"mac2-m2.metal","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":")","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"EC2 Mac dedicated host"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — Mac instances run exclusively on","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dedicated hosts (not shared tenancy)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"VPC with a private subnet"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — recommended for security","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Security group"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" allowing SSH (port 22) from your bastion or VPN","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SSH key pair"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" for EC2 access","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple Silicon Mac host types: ","type":"text"},{"code":"mac2.metal","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (M1), ","type":"text"},{"code":"mac2-m2.metal","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(M2), or ","type":"text"},{"code":"mac2-m2pro.metal","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (M2 Pro)","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"EC2 Mac dedicated hosts have a ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"24-hour minimum allocation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"period","type":"text"}]},{"text":". You are billed for the full 24 hours even if you release the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"host earlier. Plan your usage accordingly.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Important","style":"important"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Quick Setup","anchor":"Quick-Setup"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SSH into your EC2 Mac instance, install Spooktacular, create VMs,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and start runners with SSH provisioning:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# Install Spooktacular","brew install --cask spooktacular","","# Install the LaunchDaemon for headless operation","spook service install","","# Create and configure a base VM","spook create base --from-ipsw latest --cpu 4 --memory 8 --disk 64","spook start base","# ... install Xcode, enable SSH, configure settings","spook stop base","","# Clone runners and start with provisioning","spook clone base runner-01","spook clone base runner-02","spook start runner-01 --headless \\","    --user-data ~\/github-runner-setup.sh --provision ssh --ssh-user admin","spook start runner-02 --headless \\","    --user-data ~\/github-runner-setup.sh --provision ssh --ssh-user admin"]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Manual Step-by-Step Setup","anchor":"Manual-Step-by-Step-Setup"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you prefer to configure each step yourself, follow this procedure."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Step 1: Install Spooktacular","anchor":"Step-1-Install-Spooktacular"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SSH into your EC2 Mac instance and install via Homebrew:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["ssh -i ~\/.ssh\/my-key.pem ec2-user@<ec2-public-ip>","","# Install Homebrew if not already present","\/bin\/bash -c \"$(curl -fsSL https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/Homebrew\/install\/HEAD\/install.sh)\"","","# Install Spooktacular","brew install --cask spooktacular"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Verify the installation:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook --version","# spook 0.1.0"]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Step 2: Install the LaunchDaemon","anchor":"Step-2-Install-the-LaunchDaemon"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Register Spooktacular as a system service for headless operation:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook service install"]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook service install"},{"text":" creates a LaunchDaemon plist at","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/Library\/LaunchDaemons\/dev.spooktacular.daemon.plist"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Note","style":"note"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"An HTTP control API for remote management is planned for a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"future release. For now, manage VMs via SSH + CLI.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Note","style":"note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The LaunchDaemon starts on system boot, restarts automatically"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on crash, and ensures VMs survive SSH session termination."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"LaunchDaemon vs LaunchAgent","anchor":"LaunchDaemon-vs-LaunchAgent"},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Service Type","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Runs as","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Starts at","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Best for","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"LaunchDaemon","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"root","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"System boot","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Servers, CI hosts, EC2 Mac","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"LaunchAgent","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"User","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"User login","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Developer workstations","type":"text"}]}]]],"header":"row"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For EC2 Mac deployments, always use the LaunchDaemon ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook service install"},{"type":"text","text":"). LaunchAgents require an active GUI session and are not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"suitable for headless server operation."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# LaunchDaemon (recommended for EC2 Mac)","spook service install","","# LaunchAgent (for developer machines)","spook service install --user"]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Security Best Practices","anchor":"Security-Best-Practices"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"VPC private subnet"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — Place EC2 Mac hosts in a private subnet","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with no public IP. Access via VPN, bastion, or VPC peering.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Security group"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — Allow SSH (port 22) only from your bastion","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or VPN CIDR.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"IAM"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — Use EC2 instance roles for AWS API access. Do not store","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"long-lived AWS credentials on the host.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"An HTTP control API for remote VM management is planned for a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"future release. For now, manage VMs by SSH-ing into the host and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"using the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"text":" CLI directly.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Note","style":"note"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Creating VMs on the EC2 Mac","anchor":"Creating-VMs-on-the-EC2-Mac"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"From an IPSW (Fresh Install)","anchor":"From-an-IPSW-Fresh-Install"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# Download the latest compatible macOS and install","spook create runner-01 --from-ipsw latest \\","    --cpu 4 --memory 8 --disk 64","","# Create a second VM (2 per host maximum)","spook create runner-02 --from-ipsw latest \\","    --cpu 4 --memory 8 --disk 64"]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"IPSW installation takes 10-20 minutes per VM. For faster","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"deployment, create one base VM, configure it, then use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook clone"},{"text":" for instant copies.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Note","style":"note"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"From a Clone (Recommended for Fast Deployment)","anchor":"From-a-Clone-Recommended-for-Fast-Deployment"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Create one base VM, configure it with Xcode, then clone instantly:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# Clone from the base for instant deployment","spook clone base runner-01","spook clone base runner-02"]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OCI image push\/pull is planned for a future release.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Note","style":"note"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Clone from a Base VM","anchor":"Clone-from-a-Base-VM"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Create one base VM, configure it, then clone instantly:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# Create and configure a base VM","spook create base --from-ipsw latest --cpu 4 --memory 8 --disk 64","spook start base","# ... manually install Xcode, configure settings, etc.","spook stop base","","# Clone instantly (APFS copy-on-write, milliseconds)","spook clone base runner-01","spook clone base runner-02"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CloneManager","isActive":true},{"text":" for details on how APFS copy-on-write cloning","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"works."}]},{"text":"Provisioning with User-Data","anchor":"Provisioning-with-User-Data","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Automate VM setup with a user-data script via SSH provisioning:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook start runner-01 --headless \\","    --user-data \/opt\/spooktacular\/setup-runner.sh \\","    --provision ssh --ssh-user admin"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"See ","type":"text"},{"text":"doc:Provisioning","type":"text"},{"text":" for available provisioning modes.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Monitoring","anchor":"Monitoring"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Checking VM Status","anchor":"Checking-VM-Status"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["# List all VMs with status","spook list","","# JSON output for automation","spook list --json","","# Detailed configuration for a specific VM","spook get runner-01","","# Extract a single field for scripting","spook get runner-01 --field cpu"],"syntax":"bash"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Logs","anchor":"Logs"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["# Spooktacular service logs (LaunchDaemon)","log show --predicate 'subsystem == \"dev.spooktacular\"' --last 1h","","# System-level VM logs","log show --predicate 'subsystem == \"com.apple.Virtualization\"' --last 1h"],"syntax":"bash"},{"text":"Disk Usage","anchor":"Disk-Usage","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Monitor disk space carefully. Each VM’s disk image is APFS sparse","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"but can grow to its configured maximum:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["# Check host disk usage","df -h \/","","# Check actual disk image sizes (sparse files)","du -sh ~\/.spooktacular\/vms\/*\/disk.img","","# Check configured vs actual size","spook get runner-01 --field disk"],"syntax":"bash"},{"text":"Cost Optimization","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Cost-Optimization"},{"text":"The Math","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"The-Math"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"EC2 Mac dedicated hosts cost approximately ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"$1.083\/hour"}]},{"type":"text","text":" (M1,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"us-east-1","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", on-demand pricing as of 2025). With a 24-hour minimum","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"allocation:"}]},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Scenario","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Hosts","type":"text"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Runners"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Monthly cost","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cost per runner","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Without Spooktacular","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"10","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"10","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"~$7,800","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"~$780","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"With Spooktacular","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"10","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"20"}],"type":"strong"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"~$7,800","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"~$390","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"With Spooktacular","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"5","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"10","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"~$3,900","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"~$390","type":"text"}]}]]]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Spooktacular halves the per-runner cost by running 2 VMs per host."}]},{"text":"Hardware Allocation","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Hardware-Allocation"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each EC2 Mac "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"mac2.metal"},{"type":"text","text":" (M1) has 8 CPU cores and 16 GB RAM. A"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"recommended split for two VMs:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# Runner 1: 4 cores, 8 GB RAM","spook create runner-01 --cpu 4 --memory 8 --disk 64","","# Runner 2: 4 cores, 8 GB RAM","spook create runner-02 --cpu 4 --memory 8 --disk 64"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For M2 Pro hosts ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"mac2-m2pro.metal"},{"type":"text","text":") with 12 cores and 32 GB RAM:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# Runner 1: 6 cores, 16 GB RAM","spook create runner-01 --cpu 6 --memory 16 --disk 100","","# Runner 2: 6 cores, 16 GB RAM","spook create runner-02 --cpu 6 --memory 16 --disk 100"]},{"text":"Savings Plans and Reserved Instances","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Savings-Plans-and-Reserved-Instances"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"AWS offers Savings Plans for EC2 Mac dedicated hosts with up to 44%"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"discount for a 1-year commitment. Combine Spooktacular’s 2x"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"capacity with a Savings Plan for maximum cost efficiency."}]},{"text":"Auto Scaling Group Integration","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Auto-Scaling-Group-Integration"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use an EC2 Auto Scaling Group to manage a fleet of Mac hosts. Each"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"host runs the setup script via user-data on launch:"}]},{"text":"Launch Template","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Launch-Template"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["aws ec2 create-launch-template \\","    --launch-template-name spooktacular-mac \\","    --launch-template-data '{","        \"ImageId\": \"ami-0xxxxxxxxxxxx\",","        \"InstanceType\": \"mac2.metal\",","        \"KeyName\": \"my-key\",","        \"SecurityGroupIds\": [\"sg-0xxxxxxxxxxxx\"],","        \"UserData\": \"'$(base64 -w0 ec2-setup.sh)'\"","    }'"]},{"text":"User-Data Script","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"User-Data-Script"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["#!\/bin\/bash","set -euo pipefail","","# Install Spooktacular","\/bin\/bash -c \"$(curl -fsSL https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/Homebrew\/install\/HEAD\/install.sh)\"","eval \"$(\/opt\/homebrew\/bin\/brew shellenv)\"","brew install --cask spooktacular","","# Install the LaunchDaemon","sudo spook service install","","# Create two runners from IPSW","spook create runner-01 --from-ipsw latest --cpu 4 --memory 8 --disk 64","spook create runner-02 --from-ipsw latest --cpu 4 --memory 8 --disk 64","","# Start with SSH provisioning","spook start runner-01 --headless \\","    --user-data \/opt\/spooktacular\/github-runner.sh \\","    --provision ssh --ssh-user admin","spook start runner-02 --headless \\","    --user-data \/opt\/spooktacular\/github-runner.sh \\","    --provision ssh --ssh-user admin"]},{"text":"Terraform Module (Planned)","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Terraform-Module-Planned"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A Terraform module for declarative EC2 Mac fleet management","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is planned for a future release. For now, use EC2 Launch Templates","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with user-data scripts to automate host setup.","type":"text"}]}]},{"text":"Troubleshooting","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Troubleshooting"},{"text":"IPSW Version Mismatch","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"IPSW-Version-Mismatch"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Symptom:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook create"},{"type":"text","text":" fails with “Your macOS (X.Y) cannot"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"install macOS Z.W.”"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cause:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" The EC2 Mac host’s macOS is older than the IPSW you are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"trying to install. The guest version must be less than or equal to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the host version."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Solution:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Update the host macOS to a version that supports the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"guest you want to install:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# Check host version","sw_vers --productVersion","","# Use --from-ipsw with a compatible version","spook create runner --from-ipsw latest"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Compatibility","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for details on how version checking works."}]},{"text":"Disk Space Exhausted","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Disk-Space-Exhausted"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Symptom:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" VM creation or operation fails with I\/O errors."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cause:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" APFS sparse disk images grow as the guest writes data."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Two VMs with 100 GB configured disk can consume up to 200 GB."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Solution:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Monitor disk usage and size VMs appropriately:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# Check actual disk usage","du -sh ~\/.spooktacular\/vms\/*\/disk.img","","# EC2 Mac root volume is typically 200 GB — resize if needed","aws ec2 modify-volume --volume-id vol-0xxxx --size 500","# Then resize the filesystem inside the instance","sudo diskutil apfs resizeContainer disk1 0"]},{"text":"24-Hour Minimum Allocation","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"24-Hour-Minimum-Allocation"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Symptom:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" You are billed for 24 hours even though you released"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the dedicated host after 2 hours."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cause:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" EC2 Mac dedicated hosts have a mandatory 24-hour minimum"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"allocation period. This is an AWS policy, not a Spooktacular"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"limitation."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Solution:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Plan your usage in 24-hour blocks. Use Auto Scaling"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Groups with scheduled scaling to align host allocation with your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"CI load patterns:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# Scale up at 8 AM UTC (start of business)","aws autoscaling put-scheduled-action \\","    --auto-scaling-group-name spooktacular-fleet \\","    --scheduled-action-name scale-up \\","    --recurrence \"0 8 * * MON-FRI\" \\","    --desired-capacity 10","","# Scale down at 8 PM UTC (end of business)","# Hosts won't actually release until 24hr mark","aws autoscaling put-scheduled-action \\","    --auto-scaling-group-name spooktacular-fleet \\","    --scheduled-action-name scale-down \\","    --recurrence \"0 20 * * MON-FRI\" \\","    --desired-capacity 2"]},{"text":"VM Won’t Start","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"VM-Wont-Start"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Symptom:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"type":"text","text":" hangs or the VM enters the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineState\/error","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" state."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cause:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Common causes include insufficient resources (too many"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"cores allocated across VMs), corrupt disk image, or the Apple"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"kernel 2-VM limit."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Solution:","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# Check how many VMs are running (max 2)","spook list","","# Verify resource allocation","spook get runner-01","","# Check system logs","log show --predicate 'subsystem == \"com.apple.Virtualization\"' --last 5m"]},{"type":"aside","style":"important","name":"Important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple’s Virtualization framework enforces a hard limit","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"2 concurrent VMs"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" per host. Attempting to start a third VM","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will fail. See ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification\/minimumCPUCount","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" for minimum hardware"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"requirements."}]}]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Ve